rr.error

Class ErrorMessage<T extends MetaDataInfo>

  • java.lang.Object
    • rr.error.ErrorMessage<T>

  • public class ErrorMessage<T extends MetaDataInfo>
extends Object
    An error message reporter for a specific syntactic category (field, method, etc.). A summary of the reported errors will appear in the XML at the end of a run.

    See sample tools for examples.

      • error

        public void error(ShadowThread cur,
         T t,
         Object... extraData)
        Report an error at the given location by the thread Thread. Print each piece of extra info. extraData should be pairs of names-values: 
                          arrayErrors.error(thread, arrayAccessInfo,  
                                                        "Guard State",  prev, 
                                                        "Array",                Util.objectToIdentityString(target) + "[]", "" + aae.getIndex(), 
                                                        "Locks",                thread.getLocksHeld(), 
                                                        "Prev Op",              prevOp+"-by-thread-"+start,  
                                                        "Prev Op CV",   prev, 
                                                        "Cur Op",               curOp,
                                                        "Cur Op CV",    cv,
                                                        "Stack",                ShadowThread.stackDumpForErrorMessage(thread));
